    {
      "repository": "gordolio/Trio",
      "number": 1254,
      "title": "Remove core data fetch limits (already time predicate limited)",
      "body": "We had a few fetch limits in place that were potentially leading to fetch results, especially for pump history.\r\n\r\nE.g. `getPumpHistory()` uses `pumpHistoryLast24h` but `fetchLimit: 288`.  With TBRs every 5-15 min (96-288/day) plus SMBs and manual user-initiated boluses, there are well over 288 events per day. This could potentially lead to the most‑recent 288 fetch result truncating pump eventing, covering less than 24h.\r\n\r\nSimilar for fetching glucose, where the predicate did not exclude potential manual glucose entries, leading to a false assumption of one reading per 5 minutes (288(day). ",
      "labels": [],
      "url": "https://github.com/nightscout/Trio/pull/1254",
      "mergedAt": "2026-07-01T23:30:54Z"
    },
    {
